ENTERTAINMENT
├── netflix.com
├── hulu.com
├── disneyplus.com
├── hbomax.com
├── primevideo.com
├── twitch.tv
└── crunchyroll.com

GAMING
├── steampowered.com
├── store.steampowered.com
├── epicgames.com
├── gog.com
├── itch.io
└── roblox.com

SHOPPING
├── amazon.com
├── ebay.com
└── etsy.com
```

### Why These Specific Sites?

**Social Media:** These are the biggest time sinks. Research shows the average person spends 2+ hours/day on social media.

**Entertainment:** Streaming services are designed for binge-watching. One episode leads to another.

**Gaming:** Game stores lead to browsing, browsing leads to playing, playing leads to hours lost.

**Shopping:** "Just checking prices" turns into 30 minutes of browsing.

### What's NOT Blocked by Default

**YouTube:** Controversial choice. YouTube has educational content, but also endless entertainment. We put it in the "ask user" category.

**LinkedIn:** It's social media, but it's also professional networking. Many people need it for work.

**News sites:** Not blocked by default. Some people need to stay informed for work.

