## App Categorization: The Algorithm

When we see an app, we need to decide: productive or distracting?

### The Decision Tree

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Is this app productive?                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
        ┌─────────────────────┼─────────────────────┐
        ▼                     ▼                     ▼
   Name/Bundle ID        Name/Bundle ID        No match
   matches PRODUCTIVITY  matches DISTRACTION   found
        │                     │                     │
        ▼                     ▼                     ▼
   ✅ Whitelist          ❌ Block             ⚠️ Unknown
   by default            by default           (ask user)
```

### Pattern Matching Rules

**Productivity Patterns:**
```rust
// Code Editors
name.contains("code") || name.contains("cursor") || name.contains("sublime")
name.contains("xcode") || name.contains("intellij") || name.contains("pycharm")

// Terminals
name.contains("terminal") || name.contains("iterm") || name.contains("warp")

// Office
name.contains("word") || name.contains("excel") || name.contains("notion")
name.contains("figma") || name.contains("sketch")

// Communication (work)
name.contains("slack") || name.contains("teams") || name.contains("zoom")
```

**Distraction Patterns:**
```rust
// Social
name.contains("twitter") || name.contains("facebook") || name.contains("instagram")

// Games
name.contains("steam") || name.contains("epic games") || bundle.contains("game")

// Entertainment
name.contains("netflix") || name.contains("spotify")
```

### Why Pattern Matching?

**Alternative 1:** Maintain a giant list of all known apps.
- Problem: Always out of date, can't cover everything

**Alternative 2:** Use an API to look up apps.
- Problem: Requires internet, slow, privacy concerns

**Our approach:** Simple pattern matching catches 90% of cases. Unknown apps get asked about.

