## How Categories Determine Behavior

Each category has default behaviors:

| Category | Default Status | Rationale |
|----------|----------------|-----------|
| `Productivity` | ✅ Whitelisted | These are work tools |
| `Communication` | ✅ Whitelisted | Needed for collaboration |
| `Browser` | ⚠️ Neutral | Depends on sites visited |
| `Utility` | ✅ Whitelisted | System tools, harmless |
| `Social` | ❌ Blocked | Primary distraction source |
| `Game` | ❌ Blocked | Major time sink |
| `Entertainment` | ❌ Blocked | Designed for binge consumption |
| `Unknown` | ⚠️ Ask User | We don't know, let user decide |

### Browser: The Special Case

Browsers are tricky because they can access both productive and distracting content.

**Our approach:**
1. Browser app itself is always allowed (you need to open it)
2. Individual domains are checked against whitelist/blocklist
3. Unknown domains trigger the "Is this for work?" prompt

```
User opens Chrome → ✅ Allowed (browser is whitelisted)
User visits github.com → ✅ Allowed (domain whitelisted)
User visits twitter.com → ❌ Blocked (domain blocked)
User visits randomsite.com → ⚠️ Prompt (unknown domain)
```

