## Preset Storage: How Presets Are Saved

### Creating a User Preset

When user saves a preset after "Create New":

```typescript
// Frontend
const preset = await invoke('create_user_preset', {
  input: {
    name: 'My React Project',
    icon: '⚛️',
    mode: 'Legend',
    durationMinutes: 90,
    whitelistedApps: ['VS Code', 'Terminal', 'Chrome'],
    whitelistedDomains: ['github.com', 'react.dev', 'stackoverflow.com'],
    useDefaultBlocklist: true,
    includeMentalPrep: false
  }
});
```

```rust
// Backend
pub fn create_user_preset(input: CreatePresetInput) -> Result<SessionPreset, String> {
    // 1. Check limit (max 5 user presets)
    let count = count_user_presets(&conn)?;
    if count >= 5 {
        return Err("Maximum of 5 presets. Delete one first.".to_string());
    }
    
    // 2. Generate ID
    let id = uuid::Uuid::new_v4().to_string();
    
    // 3. Serialize arrays to JSON
    let apps_json = serde_json::to_string(&input.whitelisted_apps)?;
    let domains_json = serde_json::to_string(&input.whitelisted_domains)?;
    
    // 4. Insert into database
    conn.execute(
        "INSERT INTO presets (...) VALUES (...)",
        params![id, input.name, input.icon, ...]
    )?;
    
    // 5. Return the created preset
    get_preset_by_id(&conn, &id)
}
```

### Loading a Preset

When user clicks on a preset to start:

```typescript
// Frontend
const preset = await invoke('use_preset', { id: 'preset-uuid-123' });
// This records usage AND returns the preset data
```

```rust
// Backend
pub fn use_preset(id: String) -> Result<SessionPreset, String> {
    // 1. Record usage (for sorting by "most recent")
    conn.execute(
        "UPDATE presets SET usage_count = usage_count + 1, last_used_at = ?1 WHERE id = ?2",
        params![now_ms(), id]
    )?;
    
    // 2. Return the preset
    get_preset_by_id(&conn, &id)
}
```

### "Last Session" Special Handling

After every session completes:

```typescript
// Frontend (in post-session flow)
await invoke('save_as_last_session', {
  mode: session.mode,
  durationMinutes: session.duration,
  whitelistedApps: session.whitelistedApps,
  whitelistedDomains: session.whitelistedDomains,
  useDefaultBlocklist: session.useDefaultBlocklist,
  includeMentalPrep: session.includeMentalPrep
});
```

```rust
// Backend
pub fn save_as_last_session(...) -> Result<(), String> {
    // Use INSERT OR REPLACE to always overwrite
    conn.execute(
        "INSERT OR REPLACE INTO presets (
            id, name, icon, mode, ...
            is_last_session
        ) VALUES (
            'last_session', 'Last Session', '🔄', ...
            TRUE
        )",
        params![...]
    )?;
    Ok(())
}
```

**Key insight:** `id = 'last_session'` is hardcoded. There's only ever one "Last Session" preset, and it gets overwritten after each session.

